  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you know if you cat loves you?",
  "response": "Cats show love and affection in more subtle ways than dogs, but there are several signs that your cat loves you. Here are some common behaviors that indicate your cat feels bonded to you:\n\n### 1. **Purring**\n   - Purring is one of the most obvious signs that your cat is happy and content, especially when it happens while they\u2019re near you or being petted.\n\n### 2. **Kneading**\n   - When your cat kneads you with their paws (alternating pressing and releasing), it\u2019s a sign of comfort and affection. This behavior dates back to kittenhood when they kneaded their mother to stimulate milk flow.\n\n### 3. **Head-Butting (Bunting)**\n   - If your cat rubs their head or face against you, they\u2019re marking you with their scent glands, a sign of trust and ownership. They\u2019re essentially saying, \u201cYou\u2019re mine.\u201d\n\n### 4. **Following You Around**\n   - If your cat follows you from room to room or stays close to you, it\u2019s a sign they enjoy your company and feel safe with you.\n\n### 5. **Slow Blinking**\n   - When your cat looks at you and slowly blinks their eyes, it\u2019s a cat\u2019s way of saying, \u201cI trust you.\u201d You can reciprocate by slowly blinking back to show your affection.\n\n### 6. **Bringing You \u201cGifts\u201d**\n   - If your cat brings you dead prey or toys, it\u2019s a sign they see you as part of their family and want to share their \u201chunt\u201d with you.\n\n### 7. **Showing Their Belly**\n   - When your cat rolls over and exposes their belly, it\u2019s a sign of trust and comfort, as the belly is a vulnerable area.\n\n### 8. **Sleeping Near or On You**\n   - Cats are most vulnerable when they sleep, so if your cat chooses to nap on or near you, it means they feel safe and secure in your presence.\n\n### 9. **Licking You**\n   - Cats groom those they consider part of their family. If your cat licks you, they\u2019re showing affection and treating you like one of their own.\n\n### 10. **Chattering or Meowing**\n   - Cats often \u201ctalk\u201d to their favorite humans. If your cat meows at you or makes chirping sounds, they\u2019re communicating and seeking your attention.\n\n### 11. **Tail Behaviors**\n   - A tail held high with a slight curve at the top is a friendly greeting. If your cat wraps their tail around your leg, it\u2019s a sign of affection.\n\n### 12. **Playing and Engagement**\n   - If your cat initiates play with you or brings you their toys, they\u2019re showing they enjoy your company and want to interact with you.\n\nEvery cat is unique, so they may express love in different ways. Pay attention to your cat\u2019s individual behavior to better understand how they show affection!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
